episodes average 1 hour. High-quality recordings, 128k 16-bit MP3s. 

Full archive is 2.4 gigs, but is unzipped, allowing you to take only what you want, or the whole thing if you really wish to immerse yourself.  

Podcast from author/filmmaker Michael W. Dean, covering an array of topics from sex, drugs, rock and roll, cats, survivalist ideals, utopia, anti-utopia, DIY art production and dissemination, being self-employed as an artist, marriage, three-way sex, the Olympics, rock and roll, love, sex, Chinese medicine, dealing with life on life&amp;#039;s terms, growing old with punk rock grace, cat care tips, not giving a shit what anyone thinks of you, and making your mark on the world. 


Mostly interviews and yacking with Michael W. Dean and Debra Jean Dean, 
includes interviews with Skip Lunch and with London May (Tiger Army, Samhain, Dag Nasty.) 

